.TH RESIZEWIN 1 "June 2026" "A/UX Workstation" "Local Commands"
.SH NAME
resizewin \- resize an X window by name from a script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B resizewin
.I name width height
.SH DESCRIPTION
Finds the first window whose WM_NAME contains
.I name
and resizes it with XResizeWindow.  Built for poking applications
during remote testing through the agent; lives in /usr/local/src.
.SH SEE ALSO
auxagent(1), aux(7)
